comment: Gortat (WAS) makes incidental contact with Lowry (TOR) that does not affect his driving layup attempt.
Wall (WAS) makes contact with Johnson (TOR) and the contact affects his movement to the basket and layup attempt.
Ross (TOR) makes body to body contact with Wall (WAS) that affects his RSBQ.
Johnson (TOR) sets the screen on Beal (WAS) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Pierce (WAS) clamps Patterson's (TOR) arm and affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Patterson (TOR) and Lowry (TOR) legally guard Beal (WAS) and Beal is granted a timeout before a possible jump ball situation.
Patterson (TOR) makes contact with Porter's (WAS) arm on the pass and causes the turnover.
Ross (TOR) commits a take foul on Pierce (WAS).
Patterson (TOR) sets the back screen on Beal (WAS) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Pierce (WAS) legally contests Lowry's (TOR) jump shot and the incidental contact occurs because Lowry jumps forward into Pierce.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Pierce (WAS) was attempting a 2 point field goal was overturned and a 3 point field goal
Patterson (TOR) does not dislodge Wall (WAS) and his own momentum carries him OOB after securing the rebound.
Johnson (TOR) commits a take foul on Porter (WAS).
